TY  - JOUR
AU  - Berk, Jonathan B.
AU  - Green, Richard C.
AU  - Naik, Vasant
T1  - Valuation and Return Dynamics of New Ventures
PY  - 2004
Y1  - 2004/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhg021
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 17
IS  - 1
SP  - 1
EP  - 35
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - A dynamic model of a multistage investment project that captures many features of research and development (R&amp;D) ventures and start-up companies is developed. An important feature these problems share is that firms learn about the potential profitability of the project throughout its life, but that technical uncertainty about the R&amp;D effort is only resolved through additional investment. Consequently the risks associated with the ultimate cash flows have a systematic component even while the purely technical risks are idiosyncratic. Our model captures these different sources of risk and allows us to study their interaction in determining the value and risk premium of the venture.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhg021
ER  - 



